   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1871_03_09_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Heeren_Edo_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>HEEREN<lb/>JEDO<lb/>Jedo. 9th March 1871<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler +
                Co.<lb/>Yokohama<lb/>Today I have received the balance payment for the Niva
                affair<lb/>to the amount of:<lb/>Rios .360„_„ with which I have closed this matter +
                will send<lb/>you the amount tomorrow._<lb/>Also I will send you tomorrow the rifles
                that I have bought<lb/>at your esteemed account still + the bayonets[?] for
                the<lb/>rifles still stored in Yokohama._<lb/>For your black Orleans I will be able
                to achieve<lb/>7. mis[?] + would be able to sell a further[?] 150-200 pieces,
                <lb/>but at this price there is no profit in it for me._<lb/>Please let me know by
                telegram whether I can sell them at this <lb/>price, I am willing to content myself
                with 2½% commission <lb/>+ not to charge storage costs + therefore you would be left
                with <lb/>a very adequate[?] 7 mis net. If you agree, I will send you<lb/>the
                invoice immediately tomorrow together with the Niva<lb/>money._<lb/>Unfortunately I
                have still not been able to shift the cloths + the<lb/>underpants[?]._ The
                remainder[?] no-one is willing to take at</p>
         <pb facs="1871_03_09_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Heeren_Edo_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>almost any price._ I am still hoping to be able to make you an <lb/>offer._<lb/>Yours
                most cordially<lb/>Heeren</p>
         <pb facs="1871_03_09_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Heeren_Edo_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1871_03_09_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Heeren_Edo_4.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>
            <lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler +Co.<lb/>HEEREN<lb/>JEDO
                Yokohama<lb/>No5P.<lb/>⟨1871<lb/>Jedo 9th March<lb/>O Heeren<lb/>Answ[ered] 13th
                March⟩</p>
      </body>
